<p id="mwCVk"><i id="mwCVo">Books</i></p>
<ul id="mwCVs"><li id="mwCVw">Earle, Edward Mead. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=YncMAAAAYAAJ" id="mwCV0"><i id="mwCV4">An Outline of Modern History; A Syllabus with Map Studies</i></a>. New York: Macmillan Co, 1921.</li>
<li id="mwCV8">Grosvenor, Edwin A. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=DVQPAAAAYAAJ" id="mwCWA"><i id="mwCWE">Contemporary History of the World</i></a>. New York and Boston: T.Y. Crowell &amp; Co, 1899.</li>
<li id="mwCWI">Taylor, William Cooke, Charles Duke Yonge, and G.W. Cox. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=bjQYAAAAYAAJ" id="mwCWM"><i id="mwCWQ">The Student's Manual of Modern History; Containing the Rise and Progress of the Principal European Nations, Their Political History, and the Changes in Their Social Condition; with a History of the Colonies Founded by Europeans</i></a>. 1880.</li>
<li id="mwCWU"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt642" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Cite book\n","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Bryant"},"first":{"wt":"Arthur"},"title":{"wt":"The Age of Elegance"},"url":{"wt":""},"volume":{"wt":"2"},"year":{"wt":"1950"},"publisher":{"wt":"New York and Boston"},"page":{"wt":"54"},"oclc":{"wt":"14763324"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwCWY">Bryant, Arthur (1950). <i>The Age of Elegance</i>. <b>2</b>. New York and Boston. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity"> </span>54. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a><span typeof="mw:Entity"> </span><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/14763324">14763324</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Age+of+Elegance&amp;rft.pages=54&amp;rft.pub=New+York+and+Boston&amp;rft.date=1950&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F14763324&amp;rft.aulast=Bryant&amp;rft.aufirst=Arthur&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AModern+history" class="Z3988" about="#mwt642"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt642" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}'/></li></ul>

