<li id="mwCZ8">Moore, Edward Caldwell. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=F-ATAAAAYAAJ" id="mwCaA"><i id="mwCaE">The Spread of Christianity in the Modern World</i></a>. Chicago, Ill: University of Chicago Press, 1919.</li>
<li id="mwCaI">Muir, Ramsay. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=7mQMAAAAYAAJ" id="mwCaM"><i id="mwCaQ">The Expansion of Europe; The Culmination of Modern History</i></a>. Boston: Houghton Mifflin Company, 1917.</li>
<li id="mwCaU">Palat, Madhavan K., <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.palgrave.com/products/Title.aspx?pid=262964" id="mwCaY">Social Identities in Revolutionary Russia</a>, ed. (Macmillan, Palgrave, UK, and St Martin's Press, New York, 2001).</li>
<li id="mwCac">Palat, Madhavan K., <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.unesco.org/culture/asia/html_eng/volume6.htm" id="mwCag">History of Civilizations of Central Asia, ed., vol. 6, Towards the Contemporary Period: From The Mid-Nineteenth Century To The End Of The Twentieth Century</a>, UNESCO, Paris 2005.</li>
<li id="mwCak">Robinson, James Harvey, and Charles Austin Beard. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=9TcNAAAAIAAJ" id="mwCao"><i id="mwCas">Readings in Modern European History; A Collection of Extracts from the Sources Chosen with the Purpose of Illustrating Some of the Chief Phases of Development of Europe During the Last Two Hundred Years</i></a>. Boston: Ginn &amp; Co, 1908.</li></ul>

